Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.27,0:01:39.41,Dialogue Top,OP JP,0,0,0,,I feel so all in secret life
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.21,0:01:47.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We, who have come to a hotel in Karuizawa,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.54,0:01:53.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Came upon Kisaki Eri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who\Nhad come with her lawyer friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.34,0:01:57.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That night, while looking for Uncle,\Nwho had disappeared after he got drunk,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.84,0:02:02.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We discovered Usui Ritsuko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} dead in her room.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.51,0:02:05.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Furthermore, Uncle was sleeping in that room.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.23,0:02:11.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course, he was taken to the\Nstation as an important reference.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.98,0:02:15.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Us who stayed...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.03,0:02:20.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then the reason you didn't go\Nwith Dad but chose to stay here was...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.95,0:02:24.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You idiot, I've been with him twice longer than you have.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.83,0:02:27.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I did get a bit angry at the start,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.25,0:02:31.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I know he's not capable of killing a person.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.17,0:02:38.88,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,Suspect, Mouri Kogorou
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.17,0:02:38.88,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,(Part 2)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.96,0:02:35.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Suspect, Mouri Kogorou.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.96,0:02:36.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Part 2!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.51,0:02:43.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Sorry, I will pay the money later."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.05,0:02:44.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.26,0:02:48.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be exchange of money between lawyers?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.73,0:02:53.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Usui{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who has been murdered, and\NHayashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} surely haven't met face to face.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.52,0:02:57.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,First of all, I never even told her about Hayashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.36,0:03:00.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And there's no way there can\Nbe any money being exchanged.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.16,0:03:02.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,R-right...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.78,0:03:06.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And Hayashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who\Ndecided to help with the court debate,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.62,0:03:10.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wanted to contact Usui{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} as soon as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.87,0:03:15.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, he asked his friend Shiozawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}\Nwhere Usui{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was, and gave a call here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.59,0:03:18.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From the memo that was tossed into the trash,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.76,0:03:24.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And from the guardsman's testimony, it looks\Nlike they were going to meet tomorrow at 2:00pm.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.64,0:03:28.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But we don't know what the one on the door is for.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.52,0:03:30.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.40,0:03:36.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aren't you the one who was\Nwith Yukiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} in the last case?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.28,0:03:47.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Th-this guy... I thought I saw him somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.45,0:03:49.79,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,Yamamura, Inspector
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.45,0:03:49.79,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,Gunma Kenkei Police Officer
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.53,0:03:49.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Gunma Province area's idiot investigator!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.04,0:03:53.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's up, Inspector?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.58,0:03:55.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aren't you stationed at Karuizawa Nagano Province?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.04,0:04:00.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, but this place is really close to\NGunma, so we're in charge of the policing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.80,0:04:04.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, you've met Yukiko and this child already?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.05,0:04:08.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, it looks like her husband came after, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.43,0:04:12.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But they pulled me all around the\Ncase, and it was quite exhausting.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.31,0:04:14.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Especially this Musu...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.65,0:04:19.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mu... Mu... That tubby Ojii{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was the culprit right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.73,0:04:22.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uh... Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.61,0:04:25.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector Yamamura.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.12,0:04:32.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I-Is that true?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.29,0:04:38.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ma'am, I'm sorry to tell you this,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.04,0:04:41.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the culprit appears to be your husband.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.59,0:04:48.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your husband's fingerprints were found\Non the phone cord used as the weapon.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.93,0:04:53.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Furthermore, there are witnesses who say they\Nsaw your husband and the victim having a quarrel.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.10,0:04:57.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit is undoubtedly your husband!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.07,0:05:05.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I told you earlier that there were no\Nmarks left on my husband's hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.11,0:05:09.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's a famous detective, furthermore, he's a pro in murders,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.83,0:05:12.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He probably came up with some\Noriginal way to not leave any traces.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.79,0:05:15.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, just from getting drunk and having a fight?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.62,0:05:19.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The true motive is probably his cases.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.67,0:05:27.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He, who had crammed every trick\Ninto his head, wanted to try it out himself!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.89,0:05:29.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Whoa, how scary!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.85,0:05:33.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.93,0:05:37.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I leave things to this idiot,\Nthen Uncle will become the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.02,0:05:42.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey Inspector, I found something strange by the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.19,0:05:46.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look! Right here there's... Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.70,0:05:52.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you're talking about that thread,\Nthen I've already given it to the CSI.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.79,0:05:54.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thread?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.08,0:05:57.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, it was on the floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.21,0:06:01.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A thin thread about three cm long with a knot tied in it,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.79,0:06:06.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Along with the broken piece of the chain lock.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.42,0:06:10.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, did you get a close look at that piece of the chain?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.72,0:06:11.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, I saw it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.39,0:06:16.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Upon the broken piece, there\Nwas a strange mark left behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.98,0:06:18.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-then...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.14,0:06:23.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I've gotten most of the closed room's trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.32,0:06:25.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-trick?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.65,0:06:27.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.53,0:06:30.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, the evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.24,0:06:33.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The reason behind using the phone cord as the weapon,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.03,0:06:36.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Placing Uncle's cellphone by the door,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.20,0:06:39.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The reason behind putting up the card on the door,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.79,0:06:42.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And I even have an idea of who the culprit is.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.13,0:06:44.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, there's no proof.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.09,0:06:48.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, the MD I bought you last time, do you have it here?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.92,0:06:50.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? I do, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.80,0:06:51.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,May I borrow it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.14,0:06:54.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't focus my thoughts unless I'm listening to music.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.56,0:07:00.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, I still don't get what that note on the door was for.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.56,0:07:04.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? There's nothing in this MD.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.27,0:07:08.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really? H-hey! That's the record button!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.94,0:07:11.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh! Sorry about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.57,0:07:16.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The MD we have, we use\Nspecifically for recording, so I mistakenly...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.41,0:07:17.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.16,0:07:19.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mistake?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.66,0:07:21.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-wait a second...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.96,0:07:24.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Upon that desk...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.79,0:07:26.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.84,0:07:28.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.89,0:07:39.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see, that's why that person left that note.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.98,0:07:45.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, you can't stand on chairs with your dirty shoes!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.56,0:07:47.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, I'm hungry.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.40,0:07:52.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought you were acting like an\Nadult, but you're still so immature.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.03,0:07:55.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, I'm so hungry.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.74,0:07:59.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It can't be helped, can it? I'll\Nget you some room service later.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.00,0:08:03.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-hey, isn't that...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.59,0:08:10.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, Saku{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.80,0:08:15.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How did he act at the police station?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.80,0:08:18.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, it seems like Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was really drunk,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.26,0:08:21.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And he can't even remember why he was in her room.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.48,0:08:28.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The police can't even believe it, that the famous\NDetective Mouri was the murderer and was stuttering.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.23,0:08:30.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.98,0:08:35.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry Kisaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, but the culprit can only be Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.07,0:08:40.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The room Usui{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was in had the chain\Nlock on, and therefore was a locked room.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.58,0:08:43.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was asleep on the bed in that room also.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.33,0:08:46.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The way of the murder is also a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.42,0:08:51.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If he had pushed her aside drunkenly and\Nby chance had killed her by hitting a bad area,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.92,0:08:52.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then it would be considered an accident,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.22,0:08:55.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But she was killed from strangulation by the phone cord.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.22,0:08:57.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is a murder no matter how you look at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.26,0:09:03.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. If it was murder or violence, then he\Nwould be imprisoned for at least 10 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.31,0:09:09.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it was a heavy sentence, then it would\Neven be life imprisonment, or even execution.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.73,0:09:11.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-hey, Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.19,0:09:15.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were saying earlier that the culprit was someone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.74,0:09:18.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, that? That was just my mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.37,0:09:22.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, Kisaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, what was it that you wanted me for?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.12,0:09:25.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, there was a problem I just couldn't figure out,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.21,0:09:28.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I wanted to hear your opinion on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.08,0:09:31.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're a specialist in criminal investigation, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.05,0:09:34.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I thought you would know\Na lot about these sorts of things.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.51,0:09:38.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come on, let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.18,0:09:39.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kisaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.60,0:09:42.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.31,0:09:47.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, what are we going to do about that case?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.19,0:09:52.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You know, the one she was in, with the sewage problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.98,0:09:56.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you want, I'll take it over.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.40,0:10:00.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, unlike her, I don't specialize in this.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.95,0:10:03.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The most I could do is to keep them from getting buried.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.16,0:10:10.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, a phone call. Sorry, but can you go to her room first?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.75,0:10:11.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.54,0:10:15.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's see... Her room was...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.51,0:10:20.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.06,0:10:26.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, it's Oji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.18,0:10:29.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh, it's only you kid?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.69,0:10:32.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, the inspectors went home.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.98,0:10:34.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.19,0:10:38.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, Kisaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} said she wanted\Nto talk to me about something, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.28,0:10:45.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's probably about the 3cm or so thread and\Nthe broken piece of the chain that was near this door.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.12,0:10:53.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oba{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} said, "With that thread, you can\Nmake a locked room even from the outside."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.79,0:10:55.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That can't be.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.00,0:11:02.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I had to bust through because the chain lock was on.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.10,0:11:06.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How can I use a short thread like that to...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.93,0:11:10.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What if the chain was cut from the beginning?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.52,0:11:16.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that cut chain's ends were tied by the thread,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.44,0:11:23.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And if you put the tied location and the originally cut chain,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.53,0:11:28.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At a place where one can not see them from the opening?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.54,0:11:31.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.63,0:11:40.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right. Afterwards, all you have to do is\Nbreak the door open violently with a tackle.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.55,0:11:49.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The thread will break, and to us outside, it\Nwould seem like the chain lock was on the entire time.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.85,0:11:53.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right, Saku{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.36,0:12:02.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You tampered with the lock, right, Saku{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.57,0:12:05.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.66,0:12:10.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had woken up in the\Nroom and removed the chain lock,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.04,0:12:13.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then it would become obvious that...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.71,0:12:18.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why you used the phone cord as\Nthe weapon, so that the phone wouldn't ring.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.00,0:12:22.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Placed my husband's cellphone\Naway from the bed and near the door,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.80,0:12:26.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And put the "Please Do Not Disturb"\Nsign on the outside knob of the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.10,0:12:28.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was to prevent anyone from ringing the bell, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.85,0:12:33.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To prevent waking up my husband who\Nwas sleeping on the bed after he got drunk.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.27,0:12:36.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, the reason you placed the phone near the door,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.02,0:12:39.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was to make the ringing easier to hear from the outside,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.36,0:12:41.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And to let us know that my husband was inside the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.49,0:12:47.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then to let us open the door with the master key.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.33,0:12:50.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But if I didn't make the call at that time,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.95,0:12:52.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were planning to do so, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.46,0:12:55.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You are indeed Kisaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.29,0:12:57.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your words are well thought through.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.13,0:13:02.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But in this case, it's best that you don't\Nget on Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s side and be his lawyer.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.22,0:13:04.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no proof that I did it,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.26,0:13:08.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And I don't want to leave a\Nblack mark on your undefeated score.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.35,0:13:13.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You idiot, the only reason I'm still\Nundefeated is because my fluke has been continuing.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.10,0:13:16.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I feel like I want to lose once to get rid of the pressure.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.60,0:13:20.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's too bad, but it looks like it will still continue,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.61,0:13:26.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because you already confessed that you were\Nthe culprit the moment you stepped into this room.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.70,0:13:31.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How did you know that this was her room?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.37,0:13:37.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course I knew, because in front of\Nthe room, there were Hayashi rice pl...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.96,0:13:42.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, what about the Hayashi rice?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.59,0:13:45.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-that's...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.30,0:13:48.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, probably after you killed Usui{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.55,0:13:54.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,While you were still making the\Nchain lock's trick, the bell rang.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.48,0:13:59.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From the peephole on the door,\Nyou saw the hotel service personnel,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.86,0:14:02.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And on the desk was the memo with Hayashi 2 on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.28,0:14:06.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why you got angry, tore the\Nmemo out, and tossed it into the trash, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.53,0:14:10.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thinking, "To order Hayashi rice at a time like this."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.24,0:14:16.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, you left a note on the door\Nsaying, "I will pay for them later,"
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.00,0:14:23.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To prevent him from ringing the\Nbell again, along with the DND sign.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.38,0:14:28.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Unless that's the case, the words\N"Hayashi Rice" would never come from your lips.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.01,0:14:35.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I just happened to see the service\Npersonnel that brought the Hayashi rice to her room.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.47,0:14:39.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why I knew this was her room.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.60,0:14:42.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry, but that memo with "Hayashi,"
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.73,0:14:46.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It really meant a meeting with Hayashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} at 2:00pm.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.24,0:14:57.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You just mistook it with the room\Nservice menu on the table for the Hayashi rice.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.08,0:15:02.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,U-uh... Did I say Hayashi rice?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.63,0:15:05.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I saw the room number and came in.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.21,0:15:06.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, so you still haven't noticed?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.63,0:15:14.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look, the chain lock to this room isn't cut.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.64,0:15:20.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This was an empty room that I\Nhad asked the hotel to lend us.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.77,0:15:23.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Her real room is two rooms down from this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.77,0:15:32.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Meaning, there would be no reason for you to\Nhave entered this room, unless you were the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.45,0:15:40.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry to lead you into a trap.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.79,0:15:45.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because you were the opponent, I didn't\Nthink that you would go down so easily.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.55,0:15:52.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've just understood for the first time how the\Npolicemen felt that took you as an opponent.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.93,0:15:57.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, how were you planning to make the police believe you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.31,0:16:00.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The only one that saw me go into this room was you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.69,0:16:03.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your testimony as Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s family member is...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.35,0:16:06.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, I'm not the only one who saw it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.32,0:16:09.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You mean this kid?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.44,0:16:11.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not just me either.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.41,0:16:15.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, Inspector?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.28,0:16:19.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, I've been watching.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.29,0:16:22.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was as clear as crystal from\Nthis peep hole in the opposite room.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.37,0:16:26.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, everyone?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.21,0:16:30.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, we saw all your movements!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.30,0:16:34.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We've even recorded your talk on video.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.88,0:16:36.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I... See...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.14,0:16:40.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They were all his ideas, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.85,0:16:46.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, was the motive her current case?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.73,0:16:52.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, that place the factory is influencing is where I grew up,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.45,0:16:55.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And I wanted them to win, no matter what.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.99,0:16:58.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was originally planning to put her to sleep at the door,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.58,0:17:03.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Lock the room, and make it look like a suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.50,0:17:06.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was sleeping in the room,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.04,0:17:09.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And I thought a person who wanted to commit\Nsuicide wouldn't have brought another man to the room,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.46,0:17:13.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And eat Hayashi rice together happily.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.97,0:17:17.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I changed it to a murder\Nand let Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} take the blame.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.22,0:17:23.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If, in order to win the case, it became\None of the villagers that killed the lawyer,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.18,0:17:26.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then it wouldn't look good in front of the judges, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.56,0:17:31.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I was planning on\Nturning myself in once they had won.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.28,0:17:36.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But even if you did turn yourself in,\Nthere's no proof that says you did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.95,0:17:38.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.07,0:17:42.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The paint left on that chain that was a bit different, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.04,0:17:46.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There is only one paint that matches up with that,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.08,0:17:50.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And with that as your proof, you were\Nplanning to bring it to the police, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.17,0:17:59.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Usui{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} only took it as a\Njob, did you really have to kill her?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.14,0:18:06.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If she really took it as a job for her living,\Nthen I wouldn't have done something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.89,0:18:12.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I learned that she was torturing the people of\Nthe village just to raise her reputation and beat you,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.19,0:18:14.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I just couldn't forgive her.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.98,0:18:16.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To beat me?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.15,0:18:22.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, the reason she brought the drunken\NMouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} to her room was for that as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.41,0:18:25.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-that can't be...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.33,0:18:29.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To believe the requester and\Nbecome his or her lawyer is our job,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.79,0:18:31.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But you believe in them too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.54,0:18:35.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A person has a front and back side that eyes cannot see.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.21,0:18:40.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even I, who has been wanting\Nyou for a long time for myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.43,0:18:43.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.85,0:18:46.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, I won't be your lawyer just from something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.39,0:18:48.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.94,0:18:55.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Man, I wanted to show it to you, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.61,0:18:57.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your wife's astonishing deduction.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.69,0:18:59.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's what you call "The Sleeping Kogoro's" wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.16,0:19:03.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The queen of lawyers; it really touched me!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.66,0:19:06.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What were you doing at the time?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.70,0:19:09.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As requested by her, I placed the bait, Hayashi rice,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.71,0:19:12.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And was watching it from the opposite room.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.50,0:19:16.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, the moment they entered\Nthe hall, I called her cellphone.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.63,0:19:17.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then, and then!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.88,0:19:19.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When the culprit entered the room,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.13,0:19:26.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought, "Wow, I'm glad I became an inspector."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.02,0:19:30.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And... Where is she now?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.77,0:19:35.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look, she's over there, at that table.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.11,0:19:40.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.57,0:19:43.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Lucky, now I can stick around for breakfast!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.95,0:19:46.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.38,0:19:57.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That mood just might be...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.42,0:20:04.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry Eri, I believed in you, I believed that\Nyou would be able to prove my innocence.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.30,0:20:10.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, uh... I've been growing tired of Ran's cooking.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.43,0:20:14.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, uh... I wanted to try your different taste in cooking.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.23,0:20:22.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uh... Can you come back to me soon?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.90,0:20:24.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't take it anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.04,0:20:32.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You know, today is our anniversary,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.29,0:20:35.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And I thought it would be perfect, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.25,0:20:39.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, are you listening?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.17,0:20:40.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.14,0:20:46.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.35,0:20:49.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uhh... Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.06,0:20:52.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dad! Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.35,0:20:56.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is it? What were you two talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.19,0:21:04.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, for the Queen of Lawyers, I thought she took\Nrather long to prove her beloved man's innocence.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.95,0:21:09.53,Dialogue Top,Note,0,0,0,,(Sai ai: Beloved, Sai yaku: The worst)
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.95,0:21:09.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, are you sure you didn't\Nmistake beloved for "The Worst"?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.87,0:21:10.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What!?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.41,0:21:14.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I hope you learned your lesson\Nfrom this and will stop drinking so much,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.66,0:21:16.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mr. Mustached Sexual Harrassment.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.88,0:21:19.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-what did you say!?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.34,0:21:20.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.09,0:21:22.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, and Ran,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.84,0:21:27.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm going to borrow this disk for a\Nwhile; I'm starting to love this song, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.10,0:21:32.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Later.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.47,0:21:33.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.35,0:21:36.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hmph, don't ever show your face again!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.40,0:21:39.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dad, you idiot, idiot, idiot!
